OL,6,FMr Eneser said: "This case is about
OL,7,Fmuch more than compensation. Poor
OL,8,Faccessibility in rail travel is not
OL,9,Fjust a one-off issue.
OL,11,F"This is something that prevents
OL,12,Fmyself and others with visual
OL,13,Fimpairments from travelling with
OL,14,Fconfidence. I'm not always sure that
OL,15,FI'll be met with the right level of
OL,16,Fsupport to complete my journeys.
OL,18,F"At the best of times, it makes travel
OL,19,Fstressful, and in the worst-case
OL,20,Fscenario it can be really dangerous."
